<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
TARZANA MINI-MALL FIRE BURNS COSMETICS STORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fire erupted at a cosmetics store inside a Tarzana mini-mall Sunday, causing 
$45,000 in damage, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
There were no injuries reported in the 5:30 p.m. blaze at Gloria's Skin &amp; 
Body Care in the 19400 block of Ventura Boulevard, said Jim Wells, a spokesman 
for the Los Angeles Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
It took 35 firefighters about 25 minutes to extinguish the fire, Wells said. 
Fire-resistant walls prevented the blaze from spreading to neighboring 
businesses in the one-story complex, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Damage was estimated at $35,000 to property and $10,000 to the contents, Wells 
said. The fire is believed to have been started by an electrical short, he 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
