<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
1 MAN DIES, 1 INJURED IN 2 APARTMENT FIRES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One man died and a second was injured in two separate apartment fires Sunday 
afternoon in the San Fernando Valley. 
</P>
<P>
A body of a man about 30 years old was found after 20 firefighters doused a 
blaze in a Woodland Hills apartment about 1 p.m., Los Angeles city Fire 
Department spokesman Jim Wells said. The victim's identity was not available, 
and the cause of the fire was under investigation. 
</P>
<P>
The fire, in a top-floor unit of a three-story building in the 22100 block of 
Victory Boulevard, took 12 minutes to extinguish, Wells said. The apartment was 
heavily damaged and the hallway had smoke damage, but damage estimates were not 
available. 
</P>
<P>
Less than an hour earlier, a Van Nuys man was injured in an apartment fire in 
the 6600 block of Woodley Avenue, Wells said. 
</P>
<P>
The man, also about 30, suffered first- and second-degree burns on his face and 
hands and was taken to Panorama Community Hospital in Panorama City, where he 
was in stable condition Sunday afternoon, officials said. His name also was 
withheld by authorities. 
</P>
<P>
The electrical fire was put out in less than 15 minutes, Wells said. Damage to 
the apartment, on the second floor of a two-story building, and its contents 
was estimated at $30,000. No further details about the cause of the fire were 
available, Wells said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
