<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
East German Secretary of State for Religious Affairs Kurt Loeffler will visit 
Israel next week, Israeli officials said. Communist East Germany has never had 
diplomatic relations with Israel and until recently refused to accept any 
historical responsibility for the crimes of Nazi Germany. Loeffler is the most 
senior East Berlin official to visit the Jewish state. Israeli officials said 
they are not aware of plans to discuss East German reparations for the victims 
of Nazism, although East German leader Erich Honecker last year offered to pay 
compensation after talks with officials of the World Jewish Congress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
