<HEADLINE>
<P>
NUDE MAN ARRESTED IN HIT-RUN DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A nude man shouting "Hail Satan" as he strolled through a popular Malibu 
beachfront restaurant was arrested and later linked to a fatal hit-run crash, 
authorities said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Brian L. Harlow, 28, of Malibu, allegedly was driving a stolen pickup truck 
involved in a Pacific Coast Highway crash minutes before the Friday night 
restaurant escapade that led to his arrest, California Highway Patrol Officer 
Monte Keifer said. 
</P>
<P>
Harlow, hospitalized briefly for observation at Harbor-UCLA Medical Center, was 
booked for investigation of murder and was being held without bail Sunday at 
the Los Angeles County Jail, Keifer said. 
</P>
<P>
Five minutes after entering the Charthouse restaurant yelling "Hail Satan," he 
walked through the crowded bar to an outside patio and down to a rocky 
outcropping on the beach, where he was detained by authorities. 
</P>
<P>
A stolen pickup truck Harlow reportedly left running in the restaurant parking 
lot was involved in a fatal accident Friday night in Corral Canyon, said CHP 
Officer Richard Perez. "The pickup driver hit a motorcycle from behind, 
rear-ended it, then kept going," the officer said. 
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old passenger on the motorcycle, a recently discharged sailor from 
Norfolk, Va., was killed. Identification was withheld until relatives could be 
contacted. The motorcyclist suffered minor injuries, Perez said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
