<HEADLINE>
<P>
16 INJURED WHEN CAR, BUS COLLIDE IN BOYLE HEIGHTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sixteen people were injured Sunday, one critically, when a car and an RTD bus 
carrying 40 passengers collided in Boyle Heights, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The collision occurred about 1 p.m. on East Whittier Boulevard at Esperanza 
Street, Fire Department spokesman Jim Wells said. 
</P>
<P>
Thirteen passengers on the bus suffered minor injuries and three people in the 
car were hurt, including one who was in critical condition, Wells said. 
</P>
<P>
Eight of the injured bus passengers were treated at the scene and the other 
five were taken to local hospitals, he said. 
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident was not immediately known. 
</P>
