<HEADLINE>
<P>
L.A. PHILHARMONIC RESCHEDULES CONCERT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Philharmonic concert featuring cellist Yo-Yo Ma and pianist 
Emanuel Ax scheduled for tonight at the Dorothy Chandler Pavilion has been 
canceled and rescheduled for Feb. 1, a spokeswoman for the orchestra said. 
</P>
<P>
Ma left Los Angeles on Sunday for Taiwan to be with his father, who suffered a 
stroke, the spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets for the canceled performance will be honored on Feb. 1. 
</P>
<P>
The listing on Page 2 of this morning's Calendar section was printed before the 
cancellation was announced. 
</P>
