<P>
IVORY COAST, ZIMBABWE TIE IN SOCCER QUALIFYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HARARE, Zimbabwe 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ivory Coast and Zimbabwe played to a scoreless tie Sunday in a World Cup 
qualifying-round soccer match at the National Sports Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Ivory Coast got a point for the tie and moved to the top of its qualifying 
section with 3 points from 2 matches. Ivory Coast is a point ahead of Algeria, 
which has a match in hand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
