<TEXT>
<P>
More than 2,000 people attended a Buddhist-Christian memorial service in four 
languages today for immigrant children gunned down during last week's 
schoolyard massacre. 
</P>
<P>
Eulogies were recited in Cambodian, Vietnamese, Laotian and English in front of 
