SANTA ANA; 
</P>
<P>
MAN KILLED IN CRASH ON ARTESIA FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Santa Ana man died after the car he was driving Saturday night struck a 
freeway divider in Bellflower, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The 34-year-old victim was thrown from the car. He was traveling west on the 
Artesia Freeway east of Lakewood Boulevard when his car struck the center 
divider, crossed all the lanes and went off the road, according to California 
Highway Patrol Officer Monty Keifer. 
</P>
<P>
The man, who was not wearing a seat belt, was dead at the scene, Keifer said. 
</P>
<P>
Officers were trying to determine the reason for the accident, which happened 
at 10:50 p.m. There were no passengers in the car and no other vehicles 
involved. 
</P>
<P>
The victim's name was not released pending notification of his family. 
</P>
