ENROLLMENT JUMPS 6.5% FOR FULLERTON COLLEGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fullerton College spring semester classes begin today with an enrollment of 
16,923 -- a 6.5% increase over last spring, according to college spokesman Al 
Busch. 
</P>
<P>
Busch said several factors account for the significant increase in students 
this semester. 
</P>
<P>
"We've been advertising and marketing the college," he said. "We also had class 
registration for our continuing students prior to Christmas break so that we 
could devote all our attention to new, incoming students in January. Also, we 
have been adding classes to the schedule to take care of students' needs." 
